---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Container from '../components/ui/Container.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <section class="pt-28 pb-16 md:pt-36 md:pb-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mb-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="h-px w-8 bg-[#b31b1b]" />
          <span class="font-sans text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest text-[#b31b1b] uppercase">About</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight text-[#212529] mb-4">
          About NSIETeam
        </h1>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6 leading-relaxed text-[#212529]">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
          NSIETeam is a research group focused on networked systems, intelligent
          infrastructure, and emerging computing paradigms. Our work spans
          distributed systems, artificial intelligence, and software engineering,
          with an emphasis on building practical systems that advance both
          theoretical understanding and real-world application.
        </p>

        <p>
          The team brings together researchers and engineers with diverse
          backgrounds in computer science, electrical engineering, and applied
          mathematics. Our interests include but are not limited to: distributed
          computing architectures, machine learning systems, formal verification,
          operating systems, and network protocol design. We value rigorous
          methodology, reproducible research, and open collaboration with the
          broader academic and engineering communities.
        </p>

        <p>
          This blog serves as a public notebook for the team. We publish research
          summaries, technical deep-dives, engineering notes, and reflections on
          the craft of building systems. The content here is intended for
          researchers, practicing engineers, and anyone with a serious interest
          in how computing systems are designed, built, and reasoned about. We
          aim for clarity, precision, and intellectual honesty in everything we
          publish.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
